comment: Sims (PHI) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Johnson (MIA) dislodges Sampson (PHI) from behind and affects his ability to secure the rebound.
LHH shows that Covington (PHI) initially makes contact with the ball causing Johnson (MIA) to lose control prior to the incidental contact with his arm and body.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Covington (PHI) was overturned and Philadelphia was awarded possession.
Sims (PHI) sets the screen on Ennis (MIA) without giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Beasley (MIA) makes incidental contact with Covington (PHI) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Sampson (PHI) makes incidental contact with Beasley (MIA) that does not affect his layup attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Covington (PHI) was upheld, and Miami retained possession.
Beasley (MIA) and Grant (PHI) briefly engage before the pass into the post.
Walker (MIA) legally contests Covington's (PHI) jump shot.
